headline: PG Q1 Earnings Call: Management Cites Consumer Volatility and Tariff Pressures, Lowers EPS Outlook
summary: Consumer products behemoth Proctor & Gamble (NYSE:PG) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales falling 2.1% year on year to $19.78 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.54 per share was 0.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
